="1400"><media:media_html><![CDATA[ ]]></media:media_html><dc:identifier><![CDATA[2]]></dc:identifier><media:credit><![CDATA[Meta]]></media:credit><media:description><![CDATA[Mark Zuckerberg has been teasing the Quest 3 for months ahead of its formal debut at Connect.]]></media:description><media:title><![CDATA[Zuck Quest 3]]></media:title></media:content></item><item><title><![CDATA[Intuitive Machines' lunar lander begins its multi-day journey to the moon]]></title><description type="html"><![CDATA[<p> Intuitive Machines 的奥德修斯号已经<a data-i13n="cpos:1;pos:1" href="https://twitter.com/SpaceX/status/1758022464326840739">开始踏上月球之路</a>，并可能创造历史，成为<a data-i13n="cpos:2;pos:1" href="https://www.engadget.com/intuitive-machines-is-taking-its-shot-at-nailing-the-first-commercial-moon-landing-170024349.html">第一个登陆月球表面的私人建造的着陆器</a>。该着陆器由 SpaceX 猎鹰 9 号火箭使用助推器运送到太空，在此之前该助推器已经进行了 17 次飞行，未来甚至可以再次飞行，因为它已经在该公司的着陆区 1 安全返回地球。 SpaceX 和 Intuitive Machines 均确认奥德修斯号已成功部署，并开始了为期多天的月球之旅。 </p><p></p><div id="8a293116e52b41148a8b1e19cc38dd53"><blockquote class="twitter-tweet"><p lang="en" dir="ltr"><a href="https://twitter.com/Int_Machines?ref_src=twsrc%5Etfw">@Int_Machines</a> IM-1 的部署已确认<a href="https://t.co/daPrWFkVng">pic.twitter.com/daPrWFkVng</a></p> — SpaceX (@SpaceX) <a href="https://twitter.com/SpaceX/status/1758022464326840739?ref_src=twsrc%5Etfw">2024 年 2 月 15 日</a></blockquote></div><p>确切地说，Intuitive Machines 将目光投向了月球南极附近的马拉珀特 A 陨石坑，作为奥德修斯的着陆点。该航天器在阳光驱动下可以运行大约 14 个地球日，但该公司希望在 2 月 22 日之前着陆。奥德修斯是 Intuitive Machines 计划今年发射的第一艘 Nova-C 型着陆器，它携带着除了商业货物外，还有五个美国宇航局有效载荷。</p><span id="end-legacy-contents"></span><p>该任务的目标包括展示精确着陆并测试某些通信和导航节点的能力。它还将观察火箭羽流和太空天气如何与月球表面相互作用。 IM-1 是 NASA 选择在未来几年将其科学仪器送上月球的任务之一，作为其商业月球有效载荷服务 (CLPS) 计划的一部分。 <a data-i13n="cpos:3;pos:1" href="https://www.engadget.com/peregrine-mission-1-heralds-the-beginning-of-the-moons-commercialization-140038460.html">第一个起飞的 CLPS 任务</a>是 Astrobotic 的 Peregrine Mission 1，不幸的是，它遇到了<a data-i13n="cpos:4;pos:1" href="https://www.engadget.com/peregrine-spacecraft-experiences-anomaly-that-could-threaten-moon-landing-191221991.html">异常情况</a>，导致着陆器无法将太阳能电池板指向太阳并导致其泄漏推进剂。游隼从未成功登上月球，并在重返地球时在地球大气层中<a data-i13n="cpos:5;pos:1" href="https://www.engadget.com/peregrine-moon-lander-and-its-cargo-will-likely-burn-up-in-earths-atmosphere-204002942.html">燃烧</a>而结束了其旅程。</p>本文最初发表在 Engadget 上：https://www.engadget.com/intuitive-machines-lunar-lander-begins-its-multi-day-journey-to-the-moon-113535550.html?src=rss]] >; </description><link/><![CDATA[https://www.engadget.com/intuitive-machines-lunar-lander-begins-its-multi-day-journey-to-the-moon-113535550.html?src=rss]]><source_id> engadget_479</source_id><guid ispermalink="false"> 9aa4a1d7-f05c-47b4-ade0-4db13168b90c</guid><dc:creator><![CDATA[Mariella Moon]]></dc:creator><source/><![CDATA[Engadget]]><dc:publisher><![CDATA[Engadget]]></dc:publisher><dc:rightsholder><![CDATA[Engadget]]></dc:rightsholder><pubDate> Thu, 15 Feb 2024 11:35:35 +0000</pubDate><ingested> 1707995723</ingested><modified> 2024-02-15T11:15:41+00:00 </modified><category><![CDATA[Science]]></category><category><![CDATA[Space & Astronomy]]></category><category><![CDATA[Information Technology]]></category><category><![CDATA[site|engadget]]></category><category><![CDATA[provider_name|Engadget]]></category><category><![CDATA[region|US]]></category><category><![CDATA[language|en-US]]></category><category><![CDATA[author_name|Mariella Moon]]></category><media:content height="883" medium="image" url="https://o.aolcdn.com/images/dims?image_uri=https%3A%2F%2Fs.yimg.com%2Fos%2Fcreatr-uploaded-images%2F2024-02%2Fce913210-cbe7-11ee-b9f7-f4413dc704aa&amp;resize=1400%2C883&amp;client=19f2b5e49a271b2bde77&amp;signature=eb7c3e6ac4e9c73c439b070edae73dc82b6bfa90" width="1400"><media:keywords>标题</media:keywords><media:media_html><![CDATA[ ]]></media:media_html><dc:identifier><![CDATA[1]]></dc:identifier><media:credit><![CDATA[ ]]></media:credit><media:description><![CDATA[ ]]></media:description><media:title><![CDATA[