扫描的指定道路上运行。它会生成显示车道级别数据、地形、道路曲线半径等的地图，从而允许 Super Cruise 在必要时调整速度。这对于更可能有急转弯、陡峭山坡和其他潜在危险路段的乡村道路和高速公路尤其重要。</p><p>该汽车制造商在其驾驶员辅助系统方面采取了缓慢的态度，特别是与竞争对手特斯拉相比，特斯拉提供了价值 12,000 美元的全自动驾驶系统，可以在城市街道上运行。通用汽车最近推出了 Ultra Cruise 系统，该系统也可以在城市中使用，并表示“95%”的时间都可以免提使用。然而， <a data-i13n="cpos:4;pos:1" href="https://carbuzz.com/news/gm-reportedly-cancels-ultra-cruise-development-to-focus-on-autopilot-rival">据报道该计划被取消</a>，通用汽车现在完全专注于超级巡航。</p><p>通用汽车提供 15 款配备 Super Cruise 的车辆，包括皮卡、SUV、Bolt EUV 和所有凯迪拉克车型。到目前为止，其最大规模的超级邮轮扩张<a data-i13n="cpos:5;pos:1" href="https://www.engadget.com/gm-is-doubling-the-size-of-its-super-cruise-network-in-the-us-and-canada-123034974.html">发生在 2022 年</a>，里程从 200,000 英里增加到 400,000 英里。</p>本文最初发表在 Engadget 上：https://www.engadget.com/gms-super-cruise-expansion-adds-750000-miles-of-rural-roads-100119273.html?src=rss]]>; </description><link/><![CDATA[https://www.engadget.com/gms-super-cruise-expansion-adds-750000-miles-of-rural-roads-100119273.html?src=rss]]><source_id> engadget_479</source_id><guid ispermalink="false"> 6c555221-f66b-4264-8eb3-00a7e6cd8058 </guid><dc:creator><![CDATA[Steve Dent]]></dc:creator><source/><![CDATA[Engadget]]><dc:publisher><![CDATA[Engadget]]></dc:publisher><dc:rightsholder><![CDATA[Engadget]]></dc:rightsholder><pubDate> Thu, 15 Feb 2024 10:01:19 +0000</pubDate><ingested> 1707991281</ingested><modified> 2024-02-15T10:01:32+00:00 </modified><category><![CDATA[Technology & Electronics]]></category><category><![CDATA[site|engadget]]></category><category><![CDATA[provider_name|Engadget]]></category><category><![CDATA[region|US]]></category><category><![CDATA[language|en-US]]></category><category><![CDATA[author_name|Steve Dent]]></category><media:content height="934" medium="image" url="https://o.aolcdn.com/images/dims?image_uri=https%3A%2F%2Fs.yimg.com%2Fos%2Fcreatr-uploaded-images%2F2024-02%2F11fb0380-cbe0-11ee-9fef-f1f9245553be&amp;resize=1400%2C934&amp;client=19f2b5e49a271b2bde77&amp;signature=c6546c64afb008b75e02a9f47603c0ec19ac1e62" width="1400"><media:keywords>标题</media:keywords><media:media_html><![CDATA[ ]]></media:media_html><dc:identifier><![CDATA[1]]></dc:identifier><media:credit><![CDATA[ ]]></media:credit><media:description><![CDATA[ ]]></media:description><media:title><![CDATA[ ]]></media:title></media:content><media:content height="934" medium="image" url="https://o.aolcdn.com/images/dims?image_uri=https%3A%2F%2Fmedia-mbst-pub-ue1.s3.amazonaws.com%2Fcreatr-uploaded-images%2F2024-02%2F11fb0380-cbe0-11ee-9fef-f1f9245553be&amp;resize=1400%2C934&amp;client=19f2b5e49a271b2bde77&amp;signature=6c2e6afde55da117d1492b5b6a535257bd108808" width="1400"><media:media_html><![CDATA[ ]]></media:media_html><dc:identifier><![CDATA[2]]></dc:identifier><media:credit><![CDATA[GM]]></media:credit><media:description><![CDATA[View of driverâ€™s side front cabin in 2024 Chevrolet Equinox EV 3LT with Super Cruise activated. Preproduction model shown. Actual production model may vary. Visit chevy.com/EquinoxEV for availability.]]></media:description><media:title><![CDATA[2024 Chevrolet Equinox EV 3LT]]></media:title></media:content></item><item><title><![CDATA[New York City is suing social media firms for allegedly harming the mental health of children]]></title><description type="html"><![CDATA[<p>一月下旬将社交媒体指定为<a data-i13n="cpos:1;pos:1" href="https://www.engadget.com/new-york-city-has-designated-social-media-as-a-public-health-hazard-182523034.html">“公共健康危害”</a>后，纽约市现在<a data-i13n="cpos:2;pos:1" href="https://www.nyc.gov/assets/home/downloads/pdf/press-releases/2024/2024-02-14%20City%20of%20New%20York%20Complaint%20021424.pdf">起诉</a>Meta、谷歌、Snap 和 TikTok <a data-i13n="cpos:3;pos:1" href="https://www.nyc.gov/office-of-the-mayor/news/125-24/mayor-adams-lawsuit-against-social-media-companies-fueling-nationwide-youth-mental-health#/0">“助长全国青少年心理健康危机”。</a>具体来说，这些公司在诉讼中面临三项罪名：公害罪、过失罪和重大过失罪。市长埃里克·亚当斯 (Eric Adams) 政府指责 TikTok、Instagram、Facebook、Snapchat 和 YouTube“危害我们孩子的心理健康、助长成瘾并鼓励不安全行为”。</p><p>据称，这些都是通过有害的算法、类似赌博的机制和通过互惠进行操纵来实现的——使用户“感到被迫用另一种积极行动来回应一项积极行动”。该市认为，“十多年来”社交媒体使用量的增加与当地青少年心理健康状况的下降之间存在<a data-i13n="cpos:4;pos:1" href="https://www.nyc.gov/site/doh/health/health-topics/youth-mental-health-and-social-media.page">相关性</a>。</p><span id="end-legacy-contents"></span><p>对此，谷歌和 Meta 告诉<a data-i13n="elm:affiliate_link;sellerN:CNBC;elmt:;cpos:5;pos:1" href="https://shopping.yahoo.com/rdlw?merchantId=34e37b9c-8975-48da-aa39-df8bcd5badc3&amp;siteId=us-engadget&amp;pageId=1p-autolink&amp;featureId=text-link&amp;merchantName=CNBC&amp;custData=eyJzb3VyY2VOYW1lIjoiV2ViLURlc2t0b3AtVmVyaXpvbiIsImxhbmRpbmdVcmwiOiJodHRwczovL3d3dy5jbmJjLmNvbS8yMDI0LzAyLzE0L3Rpa3Rvay1mYWNlYm9vay15b3V0dWJlLXN1ZWQtYnktbmV3LXlvcmstb3Zlci15b3V0aC1oZWFsdGgtaXNzdWVzLmh0bWwiLCJjb250ZW50VXVpZCI6ImQ2ZTgzMWEzLTBkOWYtNDcxMC04NTMyLTc0MGFlZGY4ZDc0ZiJ9&amp;signature=AQAAAeaWGX1j1R5r8tv76iBsLQQ5Xm3r-ZF1UYG09JrLlleI&amp;gcReferrer=https%3A%2F%2Fwww.cnbc.com%2F2024%2F02%2F14%2Ftiktok-facebook-youtube-sued-by-new-york-over-youth-health-issues.html" class="rapid-with-clickid" data-original-link="https://www.cnbc.com/2024/02/14/tiktok-facebook-youtube-sued-by-new-york-over-youth-health-issues.html"><em>CNBC</em></a> ，他们一直与青少年安全专家合作，并提供家长控制工具。字节跳动旗下的 TikTok 还向<a data-i13n="cpos:6;pos:1" href="https://www.axios.com/2024/02/14/new-york-city-sues-social-media-companies-for-negligence-public-nuisance"><em>Axios</em></a>强调了其一些特定工具，即年龄限制功能、家长控制以及针对 18 岁以下用户的自动 60 分钟时间限制。然而，没有一家科技公司承认亚当斯政府列出的有问题的功能。</p><p>在这起诉讼之前， <a data-i13n="cpos:7;pos:1" href="https://www.engadget.com/senate-tells-social-media-ceos-they-have-blood-on-their-hands-for-failing-to-protect-children-170411884.html">参议院最近举行了一次关于在线儿童安全的听证会</a>，上述所有科技公司（谷歌除外）的首席执行官都出席了听证会。参议员林赛·格雷厄姆 (Lindsey Graham) 在开场白中告诉科技高管，“你们手上沾满了鲜血”——指的是不幸导致死亡的在线儿童剥削和网络欺凌。</p><p>通过此案，亚当斯政府希望这些科技公司支付该市青少年心理健康服务的费用，这些服务显然每年花费超过 1 亿美元。但最终，这是为了迫使这些科技巨头停止操纵年轻用户进行成瘾行为，并让政策制定者在社交平台上制定新的联邦法律来保护青少年的心理健康。</p><p>在这起纽约市诉讼之前，Meta 早在 2023 年 10 月就已经面临来自 41 个州<a data-i13n="cpos:8;pos:1" href="https://www.engadget.com/forty-one-states-sue-meta-for-harming-the-mental-health-of-its-youngest-users-162521184.html">的类似案件</a>，该公司被指控在其平台“令人上瘾”功能的安全性方面误导公众。 Meta、Snap、TikTok 和谷歌也在 2022 年的<a data-i13n="cpos:9;pos:1" href="https://www.cand.uscourts.gov/in-re-social-media-adolescent-addiction-personal-injury-products-liability-litigation-mdl-no-3047/">多区诉讼</a>中被起诉，因为它们的成瘾功能据称对青少年造成“情感和身体伤害，包括死亡”。</p>本文最初发表在 Engadget 上：https://www.engadget.com/new-york-city-is-suing-social-media-firms-for-allegedly-harming-the-mental-health-of-children-082524295 .html?src=rss]]>; </description><link/><![CDATA[https://www.engadget.com/new-york-city-is-suing-social-media-firms-for-allegedly-harming-the-mental-health-of-children-082524295.html?src=rss]]><source_id> engadget_479</source_id><guid ispermalink="false"> d6e831a3-0d9f-4710-8532-740aedf8d74f </guid><dc:creator><![CDATA[Richard Lai]]></dc:creator><source/><![CDATA[Engadget]]><dc:publisher><![CDATA[Engadget]]></dc:publisher><dc:rightsholder><![CDATA[Engadget]]></dc:rightsholder><pubDate> Thu, 15 Feb 2024 08:25:27 +0000</pubDate><ingested> 1707986280</ingested><modified> 2024-02-15T08:38:10+00:00 </modified><category><![CDATA[Health]]></category><category><![CDATA[Business]]></category><category><![CDATA[Company Legal & Law Matters]]></category><category><![CDATA[site|engadget]]></category><category><![CDATA[provider_name|Engadget]]></category><category><![CDATA[region|US]]></category><category><![CDATA[language|en-US]]></category><category><![CDATA[author_name|Richard Lai]]></category><media:content height="875" medium="image" url="https://o.aolcdn.com/images/dims?image_uri=https%3A%2F%2Fs.yimg.com%2Fos%2Fcreatr-uploaded-images%2F2024-02%2Fdbadaee0-cbc6-11ee-beff-84273cadd6dc&amp;resize=1400%2C875&amp;client=19f2b5e49a271b2bde77&amp;signature=926d06f8651f0463399f4d7ccce4bce9da5e7525" width="1400"><media:keywords>标题</media:keywords><media:media_html><![CDATA[ ]]></media:media_html><dc:identifier><![CDATA[1]]></dc:identifier><media:credit><![CDATA[ ]]></media: